The National Agricultural Seeds Council (NASC) has assured farmers that they would get the best genetics and varieties of seeds in 2020 in order to boost productivity. The Director-General of NASC, Dr Philip Ojo, gave the assurance, on Tuesday, when the newly appointed Permanent Secretary, Federal Ministry of Agriculture, Dr Muazu Abdulkadir, paid him a visit at the council headquarters in Sheda, Abuja. He said that NASC was doing everything possible to ensure that Nigerian farmers had access to the purest genetics and best varieties of seeds in 2020. ALSO READ: Delta prohibits protests to oil firms’ locations He said that the year is bright for the agricultural sector, adding that the NASC would guarantee improved yields through the provision of the best genetics and varieties of seeds. BT cowpea, BT cotton undergoing performance trial ahead 2020… Buhari reappoints Ojo as DG NASC NAQS, NASC, IITA partner to promote agricultural export Ojo conducted the permanent secretary round the NASC facilities, including the Seed Codex. According to the director-general, the Seed Codex is an innovation put in place to assist farmers to get the best genetics and also to keep seed adulterators at bay. Abdulkadir was also taken to the NASC e-library, where the Library Head, Mr Christopher Nwabudike, demonstrated how to access the website and get materials on agricultural materials. The permanent secretary commended the NASC for its various innovations and achievements to ensure farmers get the best yields through quality seeds. He promised a return visit to the NASC office to better appreciate the work being done in the council. (NAN) STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO  WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS FREE